01:06:55.000 --> 01:06:57.000
and what you do here.

01:06:57.000 --> 01:06:59.000
It should be a

01:06:59.000 --> 01:07:01.000
pleasant environment

01:07:01.000 --> 01:07:03.000
in which you can

01:07:03.000 --> 01:07:05.000
get enough information

01:07:05.000 --> 01:07:07.000
about your business process.

01:07:07.000 --> 01:07:09.000
It is important

01:07:09.000 --> 01:07:11.000
to give your interviewer

01:07:11.000 --> 01:07:13.000
a space,

01:07:13.000 --> 01:07:15.000
a field for action.

01:07:15.000 --> 01:07:17.000
If you limit him

01:07:17.000 --> 01:07:19.000
to specific questions,

01:07:19.000 --> 01:07:21.000
you may not get

01:07:21.000 --> 01:07:23.000
any additional information

01:07:23.000 --> 01:07:25.000
about your business process

01:07:25.000 --> 01:07:27.000
or about the business process

01:07:27.000 --> 01:07:29.000
of a client or a supplier.

01:07:29.000 --> 01:07:31.000
You should describe all business processes.

01:07:31.000 --> 01:07:33.000
So, there is no unnecessary information.

01:07:33.000 --> 01:07:35.000
All interviews are very important

01:07:35.000 --> 01:07:37.000
and all seminars are very important.

01:07:37.000 --> 01:07:39.000
So, you should write down

01:07:39.000 --> 01:07:41.000
information on a dictaphone

01:07:41.000 --> 01:07:43.000
or on a stenograph

01:07:43.000 --> 01:07:45.000
or something else.

01:07:45.000 --> 01:07:47.000
Then it is collected in a file

01:07:47.000 --> 01:07:49.000
and processed.

01:07:49.000 --> 01:07:51.000
Because in one interview

01:07:51.000 --> 01:07:53.000
you can write down

01:07:53.000 --> 01:07:55.000
all the information

01:07:55.000 --> 01:07:57.000
about your business process

01:07:57.000 --> 01:07:59.000
and about other processes.

01:07:59.000 --> 01:08:01.000
It is clear that

01:08:01.000 --> 01:08:03.000
you should speak

01:08:03.000 --> 01:08:05.000
in a pleasant way,

01:08:05.000 --> 01:08:07.000
ask questions,

01:08:07.000 --> 01:08:09.000
look good and behave well.

01:08:09.000 --> 01:08:11.000
But the most important thing

01:08:11.000 --> 01:08:13.000
is to give your interviewer

01:08:13.000 --> 01:08:15.000
a space for imagination

01:08:15.000 --> 01:08:17.000
and to express himself

01:08:17.000 --> 01:08:19.000
to the maximum.

01:08:19.000 --> 01:08:21.000
The form of the form

01:08:21.000 --> 01:08:23.000
is quite standard.

01:08:23.000 --> 01:08:25.000
You can see it

01:08:25.000 --> 01:08:27.000
on the following slide.

01:08:27.000 --> 01:08:29.000
In fact,

01:08:29.000 --> 01:08:31.000
there is nothing complicated.

01:08:31.000 --> 01:08:33.000
You just need to write down

01:08:33.000 --> 01:08:35.000
what business process is

01:08:35.000 --> 01:08:37.000
and then give an opportunity

01:08:37.000 --> 01:08:39.000
to send it to the person

01:08:39.000 --> 01:08:41.000
you are going to show

01:08:41.000 --> 01:08:43.000
the application to.

01:08:43.000 --> 01:08:45.000
You just need to write down

01:08:45.000 --> 01:08:47.000
what operations are included,

01:08:47.000 --> 01:08:49.000
what are the requirements

01:08:49.000 --> 01:08:51.000
and what are the requirements

01:08:51.000 --> 01:08:53.000
for the application.

01:08:53.000 --> 01:08:55.000
There is nothing complicated.

01:08:55.000 --> 01:08:57.000
But I repeat that

01:08:57.000 --> 01:08:59.000
the application is more like

01:08:59.000 --> 01:09:01.000
an additional thing.

01:09:01.000 --> 01:09:03.000
You don't need to start

01:09:03.000 --> 01:09:05.000
with the application right away.

01:09:05.000 --> 01:09:07.000
People still don't know

01:09:07.000 --> 01:09:09.000
how to do it.

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:11.000
So they get confused

01:09:11.000 --> 01:09:13.000
and ask questions.

01:09:13.000 --> 01:09:15.000
It is easier to start

01:09:15.000 --> 01:09:17.000
with the application

01:09:17.000 --> 01:09:19.000
and then go on with the process.

01:09:19.000 --> 01:09:21.000
There are several rules

01:09:21.000 --> 01:09:23.000
about business modeling.

01:09:23.000 --> 01:09:25.000
The first one is

01:09:25.000 --> 01:09:27.000
to confirm and clarify

01:09:27.000 --> 01:09:29.000
what you wrote

01:09:29.000 --> 01:09:31.000
or created.

01:09:31.000 --> 01:09:33.000
Because it is great to be creative

01:09:33.000 --> 01:09:35.000
but you need to create a scheme

01:09:35.000 --> 01:09:37.000
as we remember.

01:09:37.000 --> 01:09:39.000
So you need to clarify

01:09:39.000 --> 01:09:41.000
all the schemes and descriptions

01:09:41.000 --> 01:09:43.000
you created

01:09:43.000 --> 01:09:45.000
and you can't accept it

01:09:45.000 --> 01:09:47.000
as a given.

01:09:47.000 --> 01:09:49.000
The second one is

01:09:49.000 --> 01:09:51.000
to use a dictaphone

01:09:51.000 --> 01:09:53.000
when you are conducting

01:09:53.000 --> 01:09:55.000
an interview

01:09:55.000 --> 01:09:57.000
or a survey

01:09:57.000 --> 01:09:59.000
or a seminar.

01:09:59.000 --> 01:10:01.000
You need to use a dictaphone,

01:10:01.000 --> 01:10:03.000
a notebook, a pen and so on.

01:10:03.000 --> 01:10:05.000
You don't need to rely on

01:10:05.000 --> 01:10:07.000
memorizing everything.

01:10:07.000 --> 01:10:09.000
You need to record everything.

01:10:09.000 --> 01:10:11.000
And there are a lot of things

01:10:11.000 --> 01:10:13.000
you can do with a dictaphone.

01:10:13.000 --> 01:10:15.000
If you are shy,

01:10:15.000 --> 01:10:17.000
record everything by hand.

01:10:17.000 --> 01:10:19.000
You can use your colleagues

01:10:19.000 --> 01:10:21.000
and conduct an interview

01:10:21.000 --> 01:10:23.000
or a seminar.

01:10:23.000 --> 01:10:25.000
You can use

01:10:25.000 --> 01:10:27.000
a simplified language

01:10:27.000 --> 01:10:29.000
to conduct an interview.

01:10:29.000 --> 01:10:31.000
If you come to an unprepared person

01:10:31.000 --> 01:10:33.000
and ask him

01:10:33.000 --> 01:10:35.000
to describe the business process

01:10:35.000 --> 01:10:37.000
of your company,

01:10:37.000 --> 01:10:39.000
what do you think

01:10:39.000 --> 01:10:41.000
he will say?

01:10:41.000 --> 01:10:43.000
I think he won't say anything good.

01:10:43.000 --> 01:10:45.000
So use something he understands.

01:10:45.000 --> 01:10:47.000
Put yourself in his shoes.

01:10:47.000 --> 01:10:49.000
How would you react

01:10:49.000 --> 01:10:51.000
if you were told

01:10:51.000 --> 01:10:53.000
and you didn't attend any seminars

01:10:53.000 --> 01:10:55.000
or conduct any training?

01:10:55.000 --> 01:10:57.000
You probably didn't understand

01:10:57.000 --> 01:10:59.000
what I was talking about.

01:10:59.000 --> 01:11:01.000
So use a simple,

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:03.000
understandable and accessible language.

01:11:03.000 --> 01:11:05.000
Don't be distracted

01:11:05.000 --> 01:11:07.000
by the current organizational structures

01:11:07.000 --> 01:11:09.000
and who obeys whom.

01:11:09.000 --> 01:11:11.000
Remember that processes

01:11:11.000 --> 01:11:13.000
and structures are secondary.

01:11:13.000 --> 01:11:15.000
Remember the goal

01:11:15.000 --> 01:11:17.000
of the process management

01:11:17.000 --> 01:11:19.000
of your company

01:11:19.000 --> 01:11:21.000
when you make a description.

01:11:21.000 --> 01:11:23.000
It shouldn't be a description.

01:11:23.000 --> 01:11:25.000
Let everyone like it.

01:11:25.000 --> 01:11:27.000
We had one client.

01:11:27.000 --> 01:11:29.000
They made a lot of great business processes

01:11:29.000 --> 01:11:31.000
up to the lowest level.

01:11:31.000 --> 01:11:33.000
They were like

01:11:33.000 --> 01:11:35.000
a secretary or a cleaner.

01:11:35.000 --> 01:11:37.000
We asked them

01:11:37.000 --> 01:11:39.000
what was the goal

01:11:39.000 --> 01:11:41.000
of their description.

01:11:41.000 --> 01:11:43.000
They didn't answer.

01:11:43.000 --> 01:11:45.000
They said

01:11:45.000 --> 01:11:47.000
it was great

01:11:47.000 --> 01:11:49.000
and they understood

01:11:49.000 --> 01:11:51.000
who obeys whom.

01:11:51.000 --> 01:11:53.000
We described the scheme

01:11:53.000 --> 01:11:55.000
and what's next.

01:11:55.000 --> 01:11:57.000
I think it's nothing special.

01:11:57.000 --> 01:11:59.000
So if you don't remember the goal

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:01.000
and don't know why you do it,

01:12:01.000 --> 01:12:03.000
it's better not to do it.

01:12:03.000 --> 01:12:05.000
So always remember

01:12:05.000 --> 01:12:07.000
the goal,

01:12:07.000 --> 01:12:09.000
why you do it,

01:12:09.000 --> 01:12:11.000
your role in it

01:12:11.000 --> 01:12:13.000
and the current status

01:12:13.000 --> 01:12:15.000
of the process management.

01:12:15.000 --> 01:12:17.000
And one more important thing.

01:12:17.000 --> 01:12:19.000
Always remember

01:12:19.000 --> 01:12:21.000
that there are situations

01:12:21.000 --> 01:12:23.000
when you do it right,

01:12:23.000 --> 01:12:25.000
when you do it wrong,

01:12:25.000 --> 01:12:27.000
when you do it wrong,

01:12:27.000 --> 01:12:29.000
when you do it right,

01:12:29.000 --> 01:12:31.000
when you do it wrong,

01:12:31.000 --> 01:12:33.000
when you do it right.

01:12:33.000 --> 01:12:35.000
There are situations

01:12:35.000 --> 01:12:37.000
when you want to do it right.

01:12:37.000 --> 01:12:39.000
You don't need to confuse

01:12:39.000 --> 01:12:41.000
all three options.

01:12:41.000 --> 01:12:43.000
You need to do it right.

01:12:43.000 --> 01:12:45.000
That's why you need

01:12:45.000 --> 01:12:47.000
so many details

01:12:47.000 --> 01:12:49.000
and so many ways

01:12:49.000 --> 01:12:51.000
to get information

01:12:51.000 --> 01:12:53.000
like seminars, interviews,

01:12:53.000 --> 01:12:55.000
surveys, documents, etc.
